               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Dǝrsāna Mikāʾel, Homiliary for the feasts of St Michael (fols.
                     2ra-47rb)
 I-1) Homily by Timothy (Dumatewos), Patriarch of Alexandria for
                     the 12th of Ḫǝdār (fols. 2ra-5rb); miracle (fols. 5rb-6rb)
 I-2) Homily by
                     an anonymous author for the 12th of Tāḫśāś (fols. 6rb-8vb); miracle (fols.
                     8vb-9va) 
 I-3) Homily [by Epiphanius, Metropolitan of Cyprus] for the 12th
                     of Ṭǝrr (fols. 9va-14rb); miracle (fol. 14rb-vb)
 I-4) Homily by one of the
                     ancient saints, the Orthodox [anonymous author] for the 12th of Yakkātit (fols.
                     15ra-18va); miracle (fols. 18va-19ra)
 I-5) Homily by [Severus] Patriarch
                     of Antiochia for the 12th of Maggābit (fols. 19ra-26vb); miracle (fols.
                     26vb-27rb)
 I-6) Homily by [Metropolitan Yoḥannǝs] the Orthodox for Miyāzyā
                     (fols. 27rb-29vb); miracle (fols. 29vb-31ra)
 I-7) Homily by Yoḥannǝs,
                     Metropolitan of Ethiopia for the 12th of Gǝnbot (fols. 31ra-32ra); miracle
                     (fols. 32ra-33ra)
 I-8) Homily by Yoḥannǝs, Metropolitan of ʾAksum
                     (ʾAkʷǝsǝm) for the 12th of Sane (fols. 33ra-36va); miracle (fols.
                     36va-37rb)
 I-9) Homily [by Metropolitan Yoḥannǝs] for Ḥamle (fols.
                     37rb-39vb); miracle (fols. 39vb-40rb)
 I-10) Homily by an anonymous author
                     for Naḥāse (fols. 40rb-41vb); miracle (fols. 41vb-42rb)
 I-11) Homily by an
                     anonymous author for Maskaram (fols. 42rb-43va); miracle (fols. 43va-44rb)
                     I-12) Homily by an anonymous author for Ṭǝqǝmt (fols. 44rb-46rb); miracle
                     (fols. 46vb-47rb)
 
 Additiones 1-2; colophon.</summary>
